PO.Data: Type of machine - tiller or cultivator
Tiller - Tillers are larger than cultivators and designed for doing heavier jobs such as establishing new gardens and landscape beds and working in larger gardens.
Cultivators are lightweight, maneuverable tillers designed for working in established gardens and landscape beds.
Front-tine tillers have the blades (tines) positioned in front of the engine. This design offers greater maneuverability for working small to medium size gardens.
Rear-tine tillers are garden workhorses. They are heavier and more powerful than Front-tine tillers and their engine in front design allows the tines to dig deeper into the ground.
Counter-rotating is best for breaking new ground or loosening compacted soil
The tiller can switch between forward and counter rotating blades.
Forward rotating mode is best for managing existing beds (aerating soil, controlling weeds or adding amendments)
Yes - the item is CARB Compliant
No - the item is not CARB compliant.
